  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is the soap your great-grandmother would recognise. Lard has a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "SAP value",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "lard-sap-value"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " of approximately 0.138, making the lye calculation straightforward. At 70% of the oil weight it produces a very firm, very white bar with a fine, creamy lather. Coconut oil brings the cleansing power and the bubbles; castor oil anchors the lather. The 5% ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "superfat",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "superfat"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " leaves the bar notably mild. Shelf life is 2 years from the end of",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cure",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "cure"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Tallow can substitute for lard at the same weight; the result is almost identical.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before you begin"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Read the ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "working-with-lye-safely",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "techniqueLink",
                "attrs": {
                  "techniqueSlug": "working-with-lye-safely"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " technique before starting. Wear protective goggles and gloves throughout lye handling. Pour sodium hydroxide into water, never the reverse.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ingredients"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "defaultServings": 1,
          "items": [
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "lard",
              "amount": 700,
              "unit": "g",
