              "prepNote": "20% of oil weight"
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "castor-oil",
              "amount": 100,
              "unit": "g",
              "isOptional": false,
              "prepNote": "10% of oil weight"
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "sodium-hydroxide",
              "amount": 131,
              "unit": "g",
              "isOptional": false,
              "prepNote": "Confirm with a lye calculator; 5% superfat"
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "distilled-water",
              "amount": 330,
              "unit": "g",
              "isOptional": false,
              "prepNote": "33% of oil weight"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Follow the ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "cold-process-soap-method",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "techniqueLink",
                "attrs": {
                  "techniqueSlug": "cold-process-soap-method"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " technique. Melt the lard and coconut oil together, then add the castor oil. Prepare the lye solution in a separate jug. Allow both to cool to 40 to 50 degrees Celsius before combining.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Lard soap comes to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "trace",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "trace"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " slowly, which is ideal for beginners. Stick-blend in short bursts until light trace, then pour into the mould. Insulate and leave for 48 hours. Lard bars go through a pronounced ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "gel phase",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "gel-phase"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " which is normal. Unmould, cut, and cure on a rack for 6 to 8 weeks for the hardest, mildest result.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Storage and shelf life"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bars keep for 2 years in cool, dry storage. The high saturated fat content makes this one of the most stable soap formulas available. Discard if the bar smells off or shows rancid spotting.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
